<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="461" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,507,711]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,386,507,532]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">Material examined.</emphasis>
Two males from Islas Marietas (ICMyL MAZ 
<number box="[929,989,508,532]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" value="9313.0">9313</number>
), and one male (ICMyL MAZ 
<number box="[1343,1402,508,532]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" value="9312.0">9312</number>
A), and one ovigerous female (ICMyL MAZ 
<number box="[616,675,543,567]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" value="9312.0">9312</number>
B) from La Boquita.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="461" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,507,711]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,580,604]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">Remarks.</emphasis>
This crab ranges from the Gulf of California to the Galápagos Islands (Villalobos-Hiriart 
<emphasis box="[1376,1436,580,604]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[151,211,615,639]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" value="1989.0">1989</number>
). There are some records at Zihuatanejo, Acapulco, and the Huatulco regions (see Pereyra 
<number box="[1225,1282,615,639]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" value="1998.0">1998</number>
) and at Bahía Navidad (Álvarez del Castillo 
<emphasis box="[491,547,652,676]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[553,613,652,676]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" value="1993.0">1993</number>
). This species occurs in several habitats and is frequently found on corals. We registered some individuals on coral heads.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
